            <p>Design inspiration for this website has come from many places. The current minimalist layout was initially using <a href="https://github.com/edwardtufte/tufte-css">Tufte CSS</a> and that design approach has remained.</p>
            <p>A special thanks to:</p>
            <ul><li><a href="https://www.piccalil.li">Andy Bell</a> <small>(<a href="https://twitter.com/piccalilli_">@piccalilli_</a>)</small>, for sparking my interest in 11ty and subsequently the reason for my getting back into content creation</li><li><a href="https://ma.tt">Matt Mullenweg</a> <small>(<a href="https://twitter.com/photomatt">@photomatt</a>)</small>, without whom this website would likely not exist</li><li><a href="https://maggieappleton.com/">Maggie Appleton</a> <small>(<a href="https://twitter.com/Mappletons">@mappletons</a>)</small>, the very reason for PhotoGabble being a digital garden instead of only a Blog</li><li><a href="https://www.interroban.gg/">Luke Mitchell</a> <small>(<a href="https://twitter.com/lkemitchll">@lkemitchll</a>)</small>, inspiration behind content list designs and this Colophon</li><li><a href="https://cassidoo.co/">Cassidy Williams</a> <small>(<a href="https://twitter.com/cassidoo">@cassidoo</a>)</small> and the Discord crew for daily inspiration</li></ul>
            <p>The following websites have provided design inspiration:</p>
